700 favorable, indicating that more units were sold than budgeted, leading to higher profits. The quiz provides budgeted and actual data for a company selling two products and asks what the total sales quantity contribution variance for the period is. The variance is considered favorable when the total quantity sold exceeds the budgeted quantity.\",5\n1751,\"\"\"SALES MIX CONTRIBUTION VARIANCE\"\"\",\"The \"\"Sales Mix Contribution Variance\"\" measures the impact on profit due to the change in the proportion of different products sold compared to the budgeted mix. Specifically, it assesses the effect on profit when the actual sales mix deviates from the standard or budgeted mix. In Noble's case, this variance is $1,014 adverse, indicating that the actual sales mix was less profitable than the budgeted mix. This adverse variance occurs when a higher contribution product is sold less than expected, leading to a less favorable profit outcome.\",2\n1841,\"\"\"SALES PERFORMANCE OF THE BUSINESS\"\"\",\"\"\"The sales performance of the business has been very good over the last year, as shown by the favourable sales quantity variance of $48,144. Overall, total revenue is 33% higher than budgeted due to an increase in the total number of valets performed. The number of mini valets increased dramatically by 99%, while full valets increased by 11%. The adverse sales mix variance of $6,554 is reflective of changes in consumer behavior due to decreased disposable incomes and longer car retention periods.\"\"\",2\n1840,\"\"\"TOTAL SALES QUANTITY CONTRIBUTION VARIANCE\"\"\",\"\"\"Total sales quantity contribution variance = (actual sales quantity in budgeted proportions - budgeted sales quantity) * standard contribution per unit.\"\"\",2\n1492,\"\"\"ADVERSE YIELD VARIANCE FOR CHEMICAL X\"\"\",\"\"\"Chemical X is made by combining two materials in a special process. It is normal for 10% of the volume of materials input to be lost during the process and this has been reflected in the expected yield of chemical X. In the most recent period, an adverse yield variance was recorded. The quiz asks what is the most likely cause of the adverse yield variance.\"\"\",2\n1838,\"\"\"STANDARD CONTRIBUTION PER UNIT\"\"\",\"\"\"Standard contribution per unit for Full valet = $50 * 44.6% = $22.30 per valet; for Mini valet = $30 * 55% = $16.50 per valet.\"\"\",2\n1839,\"\"\"TOTAL SALES MIX CONTRIBUTION VARIANCE\"\"\",\"\"\"Total sales mix contribution variance = (actual sales quantity - actual sales quantity in budgeted proportions) * standard contribution per unit.\"\"\",1\n\n\n-----Relationships-----\nhuman_readable_id,source,target,description,rank\n830,\"\"\"VARIANCE ANALYSIS\"\"\",\"\"\"SALES PERFORMANCE FOR THE YEAR\"\"\",\"\"\"Variance analysis is used to understand the sales performance for the year.\"\"\",15\n1404,\"\"\"MATERIALS PRICE VARIANCE FOR GOUGH CO\"\"\",\"\"\"FAVOURABLE MIX VARIANCE FOR MAGIC DRINKS\"\"\",\"\"\"Both quizzes involve calculating variances related to the cost and mix of materials in production.\"\"\",12\n1407,\"\"\"YIELD VARIANCE FOR GOUGH CO\"\"\",\"\"\"FAVOURABLE MIX VARIANCE FOR MAGIC DRINKS\"\"\",\"\"\"Both quizzes involve calculating variances related to the efficiency and mix of materials in production.\"\"\",12\n1409,\"\"\"SALES MIX VARIANCE FOR WIG\"\"\",\"\"\"FAVOURABLE MIX VARIANCE FOR MAGIC DRINKS\"\"\",\"\"\"Both quizzes involve calculating variances related to the mix of products and materials in production.\"\"\",12\n1410,\"\"\"FAVOURABLE MIX VARIANCE FOR MAGIC DRINKS\"\"\",\"\"\"RAW MATERIAL USAGE VARIANCE\"\"\",\"\"\"Both concepts involve calculating variances related to the mix and usage of materials in production.\"\"\",11\n1400,\"\"\"MATERIALS MIX VARIANCE FOR A MANUFACTURING COMPANY\"\"\",\"\"\"FAVOURABLE MIX VARIANCE FOR MAGIC DRINKS\"\"\",\"\"\"Both quizzes involve calculating variances related to the mix and usage of materials in production.\"\"\",11\n1412,\"\"\"FAVOURABLE MIX VARIANCE FOR MAGIC DRINKS\